The Nursing AI platform uses a Retrieval‑Augmented Generation (RAG) architecture to provide accurate, context‑aware answers, training materials, and clinical guidance. 
Below is a detailed explanation of each layer in the pipeline.

📄 Document Ingestion Layer
This layer is responsible for loading and preparing the raw knowledge sources used by the AI.
Components:


Filesystem Knowledge Base
Stores all nursing‑related documents (PDF, DOCX, TXT, HTML, etc.) organised by speciality and band.


DocumentReader
Extracts text from multiple file formats and converts them into plain text that can be processed by the AI.


Text Normalizer
Cleans and standardises the extracted text (removing noise, extra whitespace, formatting artefacts, and irrelevant characters).


Chunker (sentence‑aware)
Splits long documents into smaller, meaningful sections (“chunks”) that are easier to embed and retrieve.


Metadata Enrichment
Adds structured metadata such as speciality, band, topic, file source, and document type to each chunk.



🧠 Embedding & Indexing Layer
This stage transforms human‑readable text into numerical vectors and stores them in high‑performance vector indexes.
Components:


Embedding Model (MiniLM / InstructorXL)
Converts text chunks into semantic embeddings that capture contextual meaning.


Index Router
Determines which index should receive each chunk (general index, speciality-specific index, band‑specific index, etc.).


FAISS Index
A fast, CPU-optimised similarity search index used to retrieve the most relevant chunks.


ChromaDB Index
A persistent vector database used as an alternative indexing backend, also supporting metadata‑driven filtering.



🔍 Query Pipeline
This layer handles user questions and retrieves the most relevant information from the knowledge base.
Components:


User Query
The question or prompt submitted by the user (nurse, student, educator, etc.).


Query Embedding
The query is encoded using the same embedding model as the documents, ensuring consistent vector representations.


Hybrid Search Router
Performs semantic search across multiple indexes (FAISS, ChromaDB) to guarantee the best possible recall.


Raw Results
The initial list of matching chunks is returned by the indexes.


Reranking Layer
Reorders the retrieved chunks based on additional relevance scoring, ensuring the most meaningful context is selected.



📘 Context Building & LLM Generation
This is the final stage where retrieved information is combined and fed into the large language model.
Components:


Context Builder (top‑k merged)
Aggregates the top relevant chunks into a clean, coherent context block suitable for model input.


LLM Generator (Ollama / GPT / Gemini)
Uses the prepared context to generate high‑quality answers, explanations, recommendations, or training outputs.


Final Answer / Insights
The final AI response is enriched with an accurate medical context extracted from the knowledge base.

